- The string parameter `s` must have an even length.
- The integer array parameter `queries` must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 100000.
- Each query in the integer array parameter `queries` must have a length of 4.
- The integer values in each query must adhere to the specified constraints.
- The boolean array result has a length equal to the number of queries.
- Each boolean value in the result array is equal to true if it is possible to make the string `s` a palindrome by performing the operations specified in the corresponding query, and false otherwise.